03:14.916 --> 03:17.384
No, but she doesn't have wings.

03:17.452 --> 03:19.147
Yeah. So?

03:19.220 --> 03:21.552
So angels have wings.

03:21.623 --> 03:23.215
This is just a lady.

03:23.291 --> 03:26.158
No. No, no, no.
It's... It's an angel.

03:26.227 --> 03:28.923
See, beautiful,
all-knowing smile...

03:28.997 --> 03:33.127
eyes that have seen
a thousand eternities... angel.

03:34.269 --> 03:37.432
Chloe, do angels have wings?

03:38.172 --> 03:39.139
Sometimes?

03:39.207 --> 03:40.174
Always!

03:40.241 --> 03:43.677
That's the difference between
a person and an angel: wings.

03:43.745 --> 03:45.440
Why do angels
have to have wings?

03:45.513 --> 03:46.946
So they can fly.

03:47.015 --> 03:48.607
No, but angels are magical.

03:48.683 --> 03:50.241
They don't need wings to fly.

03:50.318 --> 03:51.808
What, does God have wings?

03:51.886 --> 03:55.378
Okay, I'm not gonna stand here
and debate theology with you.

03:55.456 --> 03:58.289
So just take it back
and bring me one with wings.

03:58.359 --> 04:00.520
All right, no.
Whoa, whoa, whoa, little miss.

04:00.595 --> 04:02.256
This is a ice sculpture.

04:02.330 --> 04:05.265
I sculpted it out of ice,
then it melts...

04:05.333 --> 04:07.597
and I don't have a lot of them
just lyin' around.

04:07.669 --> 04:10.160
So sculpt some wings
and stick them on. I don't care.

04:10.238 --> 04:12.103
