and I'm not accepting it.

04:12.173 --> 04:14.198
- Yeah. But I...
- Tut-tut-tut, take it back.

04:16.077 --> 04:17.772
I made an angel.

04:18.346 --> 04:19.438
Oh, yoo-hoo.

04:19.514 --> 04:20.947
Oh, not done with you.

04:21.015 --> 04:22.243
Not so fast.

04:22.317 --> 04:23.944
Um, did you get
the appetizers down?

04:24.018 --> 04:25.212
Do I need
to go through it again?

04:25.286 --> 04:26.480
No.

04:26.554 --> 04:28.784
Are you nodding to signal yes,
or is your neck broken?

04:28.856 --> 04:30.653
Oh, yes, appetizers. Yes.

04:30.725 --> 04:31.885
Dinner.

04:31.960 --> 04:32.949
I want this on a schedule.

04:33.027 --> 04:34.392
So I want you to get
the salads down...

04:34.462 --> 04:37.625
even if the people aren't...
My gardenias!

04:37.699 --> 04:38.666
Your what?

04:38.733 --> 04:39.961
- Stop! You're gonna run over...
- Doesn't seem to be a reason...

04:40.034 --> 04:41.626
- my gardenias!
- why we didn't do that.

04:41.703 --> 04:44.001
You idiot! Stop your truck!

04:44.072 --> 04:45.664
I'm just doing what
I'm supposed to be doing. I...

04:45.740 --> 04:47.002
- Stop the truck!
- Huh?

04:47.075 --> 04:48.099
Stop!

04:48.176 --> 04:50.235
- What are you talkin' about?
- Stop the truck!

04:50.311 --> 04:51.972
- Stop!
- Oh!

04:55.316 --> 04:56.340
Huh?

05:15.103 --> 05:16.070
Who the hell are you?

05:16.137 --> 05:17.900
Kate, I know this must be...

05:17.972 --> 05:19.439
That idiot with the truck!

05:19.507 --> 05:20.565
I'm gonna kill him.

05:20.642 --> 05:22.109
I'm gonna sue him,
and then I'm gonna kill him!

05:22.176 --> 05:23.143
What time is it?

05:23.211 --> 05:24.542
That's not really important
right now.

05:24.612 --> 05:25.601
Don't tell me what's important.

05:25.680 --> 05:26.669
I'm getting married today.

05:26.748 --> 05:28.010
No, you're not.

05:28.082 --> 05:29.572
How long
have I been unconscious?

05:29.651 --> 05:30.845
- What kind of hospital is this?
- Will you please stop...

05:30.918 --> 05:32.442
interrupting and just listen.

05:32.520 --> 05:33.987
Look, my insurance pays
your salary...

05:34.055 --> 05:36.250
so if I want some information,
just do me the courtesy...

05:36.324 --> 05:37.586
Will you shut up? You're dead!

05:40.028 --> 05:41.461
Is that some kind of sick joke?

05:41.529 --> 05:42.860
Look around you.
There are no walls.

05:42.930 --> 05:43.954
Hello?
Where do you think you are?

05:44.032 --> 05:45.090
Okay, you were crushed to death.

05:46.501 --> 05:48.059
I'm sorry. I lost my cool.

05:48.136 --> 05:49.433
I don't usually do that.

05:49.937 --> 05:50.904
I'm dead?

05:50.972 --> 05:52.200
I'm sorry.

05:52.273 --> 05:53.501
Now, we don't have much time.

05:53.574 --> 05:55.007
- Is this heaven?
- Not exactly.

05:55.076 --> 05:57.067
- Hell?
- No. Just listen, please.

05:57.145 --> 05:58.612
There are some important things
for you to know.

05:58.680 --> 06:00.170
Well, who are you?

06:00.248 --> 06:01.738
I'm an angel.

06:07.255 --> 06:08.552
Who put you up to this?

06:08.623 --> 06:09.590
Put me up to what?

06:09.657 --> 06:12.023
For the last damn time,
angels have wings.

06:12.093 --> 06:13.492
Wings!

06:14.829 --> 06:16.194
Oh, my God, you're disappearing.

06:16.264 --> 06:17.595
That's not good. I'm sorry.

06:17.665 --> 06:20.998
You were saying something
about important information?

06:21.069 --> 06:22.559
Wait! Don't go!

06:22.637 --> 06:24.400
Hello?

06:24.472 --> 06:25.734
Hello?!

06:29.944 --> 06:31.002
Crap!

06:32.714 --> 06:34.477
It's coming in clearer now.

06:35.416 --> 06:38.112
Definitely, coming in clearer.

06:41.355 --> 06:42.379
A boat.

06:43.891 --> 06:45.882
He left the money on your boat.

06:47.095 --> 06:49.063
We didn't have a boat.

06:49.130 --> 06:50.154
No boat?

06:56.404 --> 06:57.428
Hold on.

06:59.440 --> 07:00.668
I'm getting something.

07:03.711 --> 07:05.440
- You're sure you didn't have a boat?
- No boat.

07:05.513 --> 07:06.673
Maybe he had a boat
that you didn't know about.

07:06.748 --> 07:07.976
He was afraid of the water.

07:08.049 --> 07:09.346
A boot?

07:11.119 --> 07:12.143
Probably not?

07:13.488 --> 07:15.251
Let me see
if something else comes in.

07:16.724 --> 07:17.713
Do you hear that, too?

07:17.792 --> 07:18.952
Yeah, I do.

07:19.026 --> 07:20.653
Is it from beyond?
Is that a message?

07:20.728 --> 07:22.628
No. I think it's my smoke alarm.

07:22.697 --> 07:24.062
Can you excuse me a second,
Mary?

07:25.767 --> 07:27.530
Oh, God! Oh, no!

07:27.602 --> 07:29.069
Oh, no!

07:29.137 --> 07:30.104
What, what, what?

07:30.171 --> 07:31.433
- What is it?
- Uh, no, everything's fine.

07:31.506 --> 07:32.473
No, no, no.
It's under control.

07:32.540 --> 07:33.507
- It's just a little, uh...
- What is that?

07:33.574 --> 07:34.541
Just a little smoky, that's all.

07:34.609 --> 07:35.115
Oh, God. Move.

07:35.116 --> 07:36.600
It's the thing in that
silver pan that burned.

07:36.677 --> 07:37.644
The osso bucco.

07:37.712 --> 07:39.179
I-I-I don't know.
Does the name matter?

07:39.247 --> 07:40.305
It's on fire.

07:40.381 --> 07:42.212
God, Dan,
you're like the worst cook ever.

07:42.283 --> 07:43.511
- Sorry. Sorry.
- Get the crab

07:43.584 --> 07:44.551
What are you...
Can you...

07:44.619 --> 07:45.586
I'm just... It's smoking.

07:45.653 --> 07:46.620
Can you...
Well, how's the crab dip going?

07:46.687 --> 07:48.086
Crab dip is going great.
Oh, no, no.

07:48.156 --> 07:50.522
The crab dip is going
spectacularly well.

07:50.591 --> 07:51.888
That's the thing
in the little red bowl, right?

07:51.959 --> 07:53.241
Yes. Can you just
chop something, please?

07:53.242 --> 07:53.824
Chopping, chopping.

07:54.729 --> 07:56.356
Oh, God, Dan.

08:03.004 --> 08:04.266
You know, as much as
I love you hovering around...

08:04.338 --> 08:06.397
and watching me while I work,
how's the reading going?

08:06.474 --> 08:08.408
- Oh, the reading. The reading.
- Okay.

08:09.610 --> 08:10.634
I'm back.

08:10.711 --> 08:12.178
Listen, I gotta run.

08:12.246 --> 08:13.213
Oh, really?

08:13.281 --> 08:14.373
Sorry about that, Mary.

08:14.448 --> 08:16.143
- I just...
- Oh, no. You did good.

08:16.217 --> 08:17.548
- Really?
- Absolutely.

08:17.618 --> 08:19.108
Maybe we have a boat
I forgot about.

08:19.187 --> 08:20.381
- Yeah. I mean, you know...
- Yeah.

08:20.454 --> 08:21.716
And remember, no...

08:21.789 --> 08:23.518
- driving on Mondays.
- Driving on Mondays.

08:23.591 --> 08:25.582
Right? Be careful.

08:25.660 --> 08:26.684
Bye.

08:28.162 --> 08:29.129
Okay, Dan.

08:29.197 --> 08:30.186
Why aren't you chopping?

08:30.264 --> 08:31.629
Hmm? Oh, small cut.

08:31.699 --> 08:32.961
- What?
- It's fine. It's tiny. It's all good.

08:33.034 --> 08:34.126
- Really?
- Yeah. And most of the blood...

08:34.202 --> 08:36.102
went into the tomato sauce,
so who's gonna know?

08:36.169 --> 08:38.866
Dan, look, I'm sorry
for leaving you alone.

08:38.940 --> 08:40.100
It's so unfair.

08:40.174 --> 08:42.472
You have my complete,
undivided attention now, okay?

08:46.781 --> 08:48.874
Stir the béarnaise sauce
before it separates, all right?

08:48.950 --> 08:50.042
You got it. Oh, béarnaise...

08:50.117 --> 08:51.141
No, actually,
I know what that one is.

08:51.219 --> 08:52.743
- Good.
- Yeah, we're good. We're good.

08:58.226 --> 08:59.250
Damn it.

09:00.695 --> 09:01.662
- Hi.
- Hi.

09:01.729 --> 09:03.492
I'm Chloe.
I'm a friend of Beth's.

09:03.564 --> 09:05.464
She gave me your address
and told me to stop by.

09:05.533 --> 09:07.797
- Yeah. Hi.
- Hi. How are you?

09:07.869 --> 09:08.893
Beth. God, how is she?

09:08.970 --> 09:10.597
Ah, you know,
still with the drummer.

09:10.671 --> 09:12.138
You are kidding me.
That guy is a mess.

09:12.206 --> 09:13.434
I thought they totally broke up.

09:13.507 --> 09:15.372
Which time? I think, it's
been like five times already.

09:15.443 --> 09:17.138
Do you know that girl Colleen,
who he used to date?

09:17.211 --> 09:18.371
- Do you know Colleen?
- Yeah.

09:18.446 --> 09:19.936
- Have we met before?
- You look really familiar.

09:20.014 --> 09:21.345
That's so weird, 'cause
when you opened the door...

09:21.415 --> 09:22.712
- I was like, "I think I know that girl."
- Yeah.

09:22.783 --> 09:23.750
That's so funny.

09:23.818 --> 09:25.251
Oh, man.

09:25.319 --> 09:26.946
Uh... sorry.

09:27.021 --> 09:28.215
This is my brother, Henry.

09:28.289 --> 09:29.256
Hi.

09:29.323 --> 09:30.290
He needs your help.

09:30.358 --> 09:31.848
I don't know about that.

09:31.926 --> 09:33.086
You promised.

09:33.761 --> 09:35.228
Well, come on in.

09:37.965 --> 09:39.728
Wow. God, Beth.

09:39.800 --> 09:41.290
Haven't heard her name...

09:41.369 --> 09:42.427
long time.

09:42.503 --> 09:44.733
Um, how can I help you?

09:47.174 --> 09:48.436
I don't know if you can.

09:49.377 --> 09:52.244
Henry's fiancée passed away
about a year ago...

09:52.313 --> 09:54.281
on their wedding day.

09:54.348 --> 09:56.145
Oh, my God. I'm so sorry.

09:56.217 --> 09:57.343
Thank you.

09:57.418 --> 09:58.783
I hope you don't mind me asking,
but how, um...

09:58.853 --> 09:59.877
How did it happen?

10:00.988 --> 10:02.546
She was crushed by an angel...

10:03.658 --> 10:06.149
and as sad as I am,
I do appreciate the irony.

10:07.361 --> 10:09.295
And, well, he's just...

10:09.363 --> 10:10.762
He's not moving on.

10:10.831 --> 10:12.230
I don't think that's so unusual.

10:12.300 --> 10:13.494
You've changed.

10:13.567 --> 10:14.795
You don't smile.

10:14.869 --> 10:16.769
You don't leave your apartment.

10:16.837 --> 10:17.929
I like my apartment.

10:18.005 --> 10:19.836
Nobody hassles me
if I don't smile there.

10:20.508 --> 10:22.442
He's not letting go,
and I was just thinking...

10:22.510 --> 10:26.207
that maybe if he communicated
with his fiancée, Kate...

10:26.280 --> 10:28.908
that, um, maybe she would,
you know...

10:28.983 --> 10:31.679
convince him that it's okay
for him to move on in his life.

10:32.820 --> 10:33.946
Is that what you want?

10:34.021 --> 10:35.420
That's what she wants.

10:35.489 --> 10:36.786
And once she gets an idea
in her head...

10:36.857 --> 10:38.290
it's best to just...

10:38.359 --> 10:40.884
I'm here, so, you know.

10:42.029 --> 10:44.293
Okay. All right.

10:44.365 --> 10:46.128
Well, let's give it a shot.

10:47.501 --> 10:50.527
Um, how do you get
into all of this?

10:50.604 --> 10:51.696
Oh, what?
You mean, like being a psychic?

10:51.772 --> 10:52.739
Yeah.

10:52.807 --> 10:54.035
Why? You think it's crap?

10:54.775 --> 10:56.003
No. I keep an open mind.

10:56.077 --> 10:58.136
I mean, there are plenty
of things people can't explain.

10:58.212 --> 10:59.338
You can be honest.

11:00.214 --> 11:02.478
Not crap, just unproven...

11:03.384 --> 11:06.012
after hundreds of years
and thousands of studies.

11:07.355 --> 11:08.583
But you're keeping an open mind.

11:08.656 --> 11:09.680
Isn't it obvious?

11:12.093 --> 11:13.651
Well, what do you do
for a living?

11:13.728 --> 11:16.219
- I'm a vet.
- So a man of science?

11:16.297 --> 11:17.958
I suppose I am.

11:18.032 --> 11:19.158
Do you believe in heaven?

11:20.001 --> 11:21.195
Jury's out.

11:21.869 --> 11:23.302
Wow.

11:23.371 --> 11:25.771
See, that's just...
That's depressing to me.

11:25.840 --> 11:27.899
I mean, what a sad and
hopeless world it would be...

11:27.975 --> 11:29.602
if that was the case.

11:29.677 --> 11:32.737
I really believe that the people
we love never really leave us.

11:32.813 --> 11:35.338
You know, they're...
They're always watchin' over us.

11:35.983 --> 11:38.543
And then, sometimes,
if we're lucky...

11:38.619 --> 11:40.177
we get to talk to them.

11:42.490 --> 11:43.616
So have you had
a lot of luck with this?

11:43.691 --> 11:45.056
Sometimes yes, sometimes no.

11:45.126 --> 11:46.354
I know that's
not very scientific...

11:46.427 --> 11:47.416
but when it works...

11:47.495 --> 11:49.224
it really does
make people happy.

11:52.433 --> 11:53.491
You wanna give it a go?

11:55.970 --> 11:57.369
Okay. Give me your hands.

11:58.339 --> 11:59.704
Does this cost extra?

11:59.774 --> 12:02.675
Do you always use humor to cope
with uncomfortable situations?

12:02.743 --> 12:05.234
That reminds of this time
two rabbis walked into a bar.

12:05.312 --> 12:07.837
All right.
Come on, give me your hands.

12:09.884 --> 12:12.284
Now, just think about the person
you're trying to contact.

12:13.621 --> 12:15.885
I am getting something, um,
but it's...

12:15.956 --> 12:16.980
But it's a man.

12:17.825 --> 12:21.784
He's in a, like, a blue suit
or, um, like a uniform.

12:21.862 --> 12:23.989
My father wore blue suits.

12:24.065 --> 12:25.032
He was a lawyer.

12:25.099 --> 12:26.464
Are you trying to contact him?

12:27.435 --> 12:29.300
No. He's still alive.

12:29.370 --> 12:31.133
- Retired.
- Oh.

12:31.205 --> 12:32.502
At least,
I think he's still alive.

12:32.573 --> 12:34.336
I haven't spoken with him
since last night.

12:34.408 --> 12:35.534
Maybe something happened
this morning.

12:35.609 --> 12:37.042
All right. Look, I get it.

12:37.111 --> 12:38.772
You don't believe in this stuff,
and you probably think...

12:38.846 --> 12:41.007
I'm some loon
who's just wasting your time.

12:41.082 --> 12:43.983
But you know what?
You're here, so why not?

12:44.051 --> 12:46.315
All I'm asking for is five
minutes for you to humor me.

12:48.889 --> 12:50.015
You're right. I'm sorry.

12:50.091 --> 12:51.149
Okay.

12:52.760 --> 12:55.058
Just relax. Give it a go.

12:58.566 --> 13:00.761
Okay. Just think about Kate.

13:00.835 --> 13:04.362
Picture her in your mind:
the way she made you feel...

13:04.438 --> 13:05.803
the way she looked.

13:05.873 --> 13:07.670
Think about Kate.

13:19.687 --> 13:21.712
- Oh, God.
- That didn't sound good.

